                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12717414" author="phunt" created="Mon, 8 Jun 2009 22:17:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;this patch includes a test that shows the problem. I&apos;m not certain how to fix it though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, it seems like access to authInfo should be synchronized - since multiple threads are potentially&lt;br/&gt;
accessing it at the same time (client &amp;amp; sendthread for example)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12717415" author="phunt" created="Mon, 8 Jun 2009 22:18:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben can you take a look at this? The basic problem is that the authinfo is sent to&lt;br/&gt;
the server during primeconnection, if the client adds auth after this, but before the&lt;br/&gt;
connection is fully established, the authinfo is not transmitted to the server until&lt;br/&gt;
the next reconnect. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should verify the c client as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
